[3] Romania
Date: Mon 18 Sep 2017
Source: Romania Insider [edited]
https://www.romania-insider.com/romania-new-measles-cases/


Romanian doctors diagnosed about 130 new measles cases in the last week, according to the National Center for Surveillance and Control of Communicable Diseases (CNSCBT). No deaths were recorded during this period.

The measles outbreak began last fall [2016] in Romania. Over 9200 measles cases have been registered until Fri 15 Sep 2017, and 34 people died during these months. The biggest number of measles cases occurred in the 0-9 age group.

Of the deaths, 9 occurred in Timis county, whereas 7 of them were in Dolj county. The disease has spread to 41 counties. Tulcea is the only county in Romania where no measles case has been yet recorded.

Measles is an infectious disease that often leads to complications. One in 4 people who have measles needs hospitalization. The disease is deadly for 1 out of 1000 measles patients.

--
